gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Clippers 124, Spurs 99
gameRecap.excerpt: The Clippers defeated the Spurs, 124-99. Paul George recorded 28 points, six assists, and five rebounds for the Clippers, while Kawhi Leonard (21 points, four rebounds) and Norman Powell (19 points, five rebounds) combined for 40 points in the victory. Keldon Johnson tallied 22 points and 10 rebounds for the Spurs in the losing effort. The Clippers improve to 5-7 in the regular season, while the Spurs fall to 3-11.
